A '''decon droid''' was a [[Droid/Legends|droid]] that was utilized to clean environments of toxic materials so that an area could become safe for living beings. Basic decon droids were squat and box shaped, with internal decontamination chambers. They were designed to scoop up contaminated material, such as [[Radiation/Legends|irradiated]] soil, running it through a series of [[catalytic processor]]s to clean and decontaminate it before ejecting the cleansed material. Decon droids were also used to decontaminate radiation-filled [[Starship/Legends|starships]] by releasing [[radiation-absorbing foam]] then gathering it up and rendering it inert. During the exploration and colonization era of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]], decon droids were routinely employed to process [[Alien/Legends|alien]] soil with hazardous chemicals and minerals. One model of decon droid was [[Industrial Automaton/Legends|Industrial Automaton's]] [[Decon III]], which the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] deployed on [[Honoghr/Legends|Honoghr]].<ref name="DFR">''[[Dark Force Rising Sourcebook]]''</ref> Decon droids were employed on [[Elrood/Legends|Elrood]] where they regularly decontaminated incoming starships.<ref name="PoG3">''[[Planets of the Galaxy, Volume Three]]''</ref>

